<br>
I have been thinking about what to do next.  Here is my situation.  I just hit 57 yesterday.  I have no flags.  I have only been to PoP a couple of times (PoN, PoD).  I am also unguilded which I think does hurt me.  I do a /who wiz 50 60 all and I am the only one unguilded.  I guess its just fear of committment.  I like guilds but have a hard time making the final decision.  <br>
<br>
I do have a idea of what I want to do for advancement.  I'm moving to hit 60 as fast as I can.  Afterward I want to start doing AA and get some abilities.  I already have run3 and regen3.  I'm looking to get SCF3, SCM3, maybe SCS and MC (at least MC1), then SCFM and Allegiant Familiar.  How long I might stay at 60 is unclear.  I have read that exp in many areas other than PoP drops off significantly after 60.  <br>
<br>
I am not rich by any means but I do appreciate little I do have.  Being unguilded leads to some roundabout ways of getting access to some places.  I am somewhat leery about 60 due to the availability of level 60 spells.  I have had Ice Spear of Solist sitting around gathering dust, that is the only level 60 spell I have.<br>
<br>
